Algeria is still a country with one of the highest suicide rates in the world. Tunisian revolution has been very positive for us, but it undermined the Algerian one, of which the Queens of the Hearts have been handling the stats wrong.

Combativity !

Why are Algerians outraged ? Its because they grew up and realized that the “Algeria of tomorrow” is the work and caregiving of its youth. The biggest mistakes are human mistakes . You have entered 1200 years of feudalism, nothing changes overnight, nor can be solved by low quality political processes during a dictatorship otherwise not representative without involving a positive human revolution.

There is no more welfare: you are on your own, the mourners. It brakes our heart, if not since countless people have dreamed of Algeria in a free state and realized fighting for it.

Wait until you have done your part, put your energy to good use, before you leave Algeria and turn your back on a nation, not in 1962, not in 1988 either, it didn’t start yesterday.
